Comment: im_a_oncer said "So a while ago I grew out of my best friend. For 5 months she didn't say a word to me. When we made plans she wouldn't show up. She would act completely different around me. When her other friends were around I would either be completely ignored or be treated like a 2 year old. I got a text from her every 3 months. When we would hang out and she would actually bother to show up we would spend what felt like forever doing "remember when's" instead of making new memories. For a long time I thought it was my fault, that I was doing something wrong. So I got very depressed. And then one day I realized something. That if I would stop putting an effort into that friendship their wouldn't be any friendship because it was my effort alone. So I let go. I stopped trying to hold onto something that was and no longer is. And slowly I started to become happier. And I honestly think that I am better off without her. Yes it's true that sometimes I miss her and the times that we shared together but I also know I am happier like this. You might think that this is pointless for you to read but you should know this is the first time I have ever admitted this to anyone. So thanks if you actually careüòò"

Comment: emiliesdoors said "January 1. The most popular day of the year to start something new, with the intention of continuing and maintaining the new habit, project, etc until the end of foreseeable time. It all started when I was in Morocco, but we‚Äôll get to that later. For now, lets focus on January 1, 2015.

Every year, I begin the year with a Bloody Mary and oysters. It‚Äôs one of my favorite traditions, slightly celebratory in nature but not too ostentatious. Not that I‚Äôm afraid of being ostentatious, but more on that later. I‚Äôve never gone to the same place for my January 1 meal‚Äîwhich is more of a happy accident than anything else‚Äîso I spent the first few waking hours of 2015 thinking of places to go this evening. And by that I mean from 2 - 4pm, after waking up at 1pm, post 4am return from various NYE parties, shindigs, etc, but more on those later. I texted my bffl (actually for life, but more on that later) @sacreath and made plans to go to @jeffreysgrocery at the trendy time of 9pm for a January 1 dinner of Bloody Mary‚Äôs and oysters. 
Over our respective Bloodys, Sammy and I discussed our plans, hopes, promises, and dreams for 2015 including (but not limited to) more time in gyms, less time ordering Seamless, a backpacking adventure, new jobs, pictures of doors, and karaoke. Guys, it‚Äôs going to be a wild ride and you‚Äôll hear about it all (and more) here.

Comment: imjonjon said "Things I wanna forget about 2014. Late night bike riding and coming in contact with a moving vehicle at 25mph nearly head on slamming my right shoulder, ripping off the driver side car mirror,  flying off my bike doing a 720 spin in the air, landing on my back while the back of my helmet plants the pavement at full speed. I got back up immediately with my body bruised, startled and shaken up. Lost my vision for 5 minutes, gained consciousness, then lost it again for another 2. That day wasn't fun at all. Just a laceration on my right knee and contusion to my right shoulder. I'm blessed to be alive and thankful for everything before me.
